author: @paucalaf5056
text: Yo no puedo ir repitiendo lo mismo a todo el mundo. Su barba me gusta y es sanísima pero debe quitarse todas estas cosas de la boca las cuales pueden hacer que se atragante o se le metan en el estomago si se despegan por mala suerte. Debe dejar de beber un tiempo y de fumar también. Creo que ha bebido mucho y a fumado mucho también. Necesita un descanso. La cama ayuda con las adicciones como el tabaco, quédate en la cama unos días y intenta apartarte de las rutinas que mezclabas con el tabaco un par de días, levántate par ir al baño y moverte un poco ya que tampoco es bueno estar estirado todo el tiempo y hay que respirar aire de la calle cada ciertas horas también. Yo empezaría con el alcohol y date una semana de fumar para no quitar tantas cosas de golpe, si fumas petas pues fúmate uno por la noche de vez en cuando si tienes mucho mono pero el tabaco fuera unos días para empezar, seguro que recaes pero a la semana lo vuelves a intentar y se consigue. También tienes que luchar con tu mente ya que de vez en cuando te dice que un cigarro no pasa nada y seguramente que no pasa nada pero mejor negarte y aguantar. Ya volverás a fumar mas adelante cuando estés limpio. Esta claro que todo esto es adaptable a cada persona pero a mi es lo que me funciona. Yo llevo dos días o tres sin fumar y hoy ya me apetecía de verdad uno pero me niego, eso si, mañana me fumo uno porque es navidad pero con negarme hoy ya veo que podre conseguirlo sin mucha dificultad, a partir de mañana lo alargaremos a una semana mínimo.

author: @RebelandRomanceOfficial
text:
Austin, you’re one of the most humble artist out there & you’re setting an example. Other artist are starting to do the same. Doja is a humble queen as well. 
I love all of your collabs, EXCEPT for one… dare I say? I’m pretty sure most people know which one I’m talking about.I wish you would’ve done that track on your own, I mean, you pretty did anyway…) 
And 21 Savage - I’ve been following him him since the beginning, long ago. His voice is unique & I love it - I can list a ton of collabs that rock my world ( Ozzy, Halsey.)

You’re facking amazing, but you already know that. A heart of gold, compassionate, engaging.  
Amazing Album - this has a deep, personal vibe & I love the richness in your voice, the deeper, darker chords that are used give me chills, the emotion is powerful. You’ve grown so much with your music & as an artist. - Hollywood’s Bleeding is still my favourite albumn and of course several songs from Stoney & B&B. I can’t wait to see what you create next. XOXO

author: @SM-yu4hd
text:
Trust in Jesus, Hell is real and eternal! This is what the Bible says about it.. 
"The Son of Man will send out his angels, and they will weed out of his kingdom everything that causes sin and all who do evil. They will throw them into the blazing furnace, where there will be weeping and gnashing of teeth." Matthew 13: 41-42
Jesus Christ is the only way to heaven "I am the way, the truth, and the life no one comes to the father but by me."  John 14:6   Ask God to reveal this to you- He will! 
"For all have sinned and fall short of the glory of God." Romans 3:23 ADMIT THAT YOU'RE A SINNER. We've all broken God's laws and ten commandments.. "Thou shalt not lie, steal, covet, dishonor parents, take God's name in vain.."(Exodus 20) We do not have righteousness on our own to get to heaven, "God made him (Jesus) who had no sin to be sin for us, so that in him we might become the righteousness of God." 2 Cor. 5:21 Godly sorrow leads to genuine repentance for sinning against the righteous God and there is a change of heart, we change our mind and God changes our hearts and regenerates us from the inside out. God is deadly serious about sin, when we genuinely repent we hate sin just as God hates it, and we turn away from it.
"But God commended His love toward us, in that while we were yet sinners Christ died for us." Romans 5:8 BELIEVE IN YOUR HEART THAT JESUS CHRIST DIED FOR YOUR SINS, WAS BURIED, AND THAT GOD RAISED JESUS FROM THE DEAD. This is trusting with all of your heart that Jesus Christ is who he said he was. He saves us from sin and hell and brings us into a relationship with him. We become God's children. We are saved from hell, eternal death.
"For whosoever shall call on the name of the Lord shall be saved." Romans 10:13 CALL UPON THE NAME OF THE LORD. Every single person who ever lived since Adam will bend their knee and confess with their mouth that Jesus Christ is Lord, the Lord of Lords and the King of Kings.
Read the Bible, Walk with the Lord and give your life to Him!

The Eye of Ra can be equated with the disk of the sun, with the cobras coiled around the disk, and with the white and red crowns of Upper and Lower Egypt.
The Eye of Ra or Eye of Re is a being in ancient Egyptian mythology that functions as a feminine counterpart to the sun god Ra and a violent force that subdues his enemies. The eye is an extension of Ra's power, equated with the disk of the sun, but it often behaves as an independent goddess. This goddess can be equated with several particular deities, including Hathor, Sekhmet, Bastet, Raet-Tawy, and Mut. The eye goddess acts as mother, sibling, consort, and daughter of the sun god. I was able to heal and strengthen myself by getting closer to God and my faith and I was able to shift my perception, change my circle, and modify my behaviors to create a different path. When I hear his music, it reminds me of the d3@ath of my old self and truly how much better my life is. I feel his pain and remembering my own pain helps me truly appreciate and want to live this life, finally.

author: @user-jz2bq3xw9u
text:
Trust in Jesus, Hell is real and eternal! This is what the Bible says about it.. 
"The Son of Man will send out his angels, and they will weed out of his kingdom everything that causes sin and all who do evil. They will throw them into the blazing furnace, where there will be weeping and gnashing of teeth." Matthew 13: 41-42
Jesus Christ is the only way to heaven "I am the way, the truth, and the life no one comes to the father but by me."  John 14:6   Ask God to reveal this to you- He will! 
"For all have sinned and fall short of the glory of God." Romans 3:23 ADMIT THAT YOU'RE A SINNER. We've all broken God's laws and ten commandments.. "Thou shalt not lie, steal, covet, dishonor parents, take God's name in vain.."(Exodus 20) We do not have righteousness on our own to get to heaven, "God made him (Jesus) who had no sin to be sin for us, so that in him we might become the righteousness of God." 2 Cor. 5:21 Godly sorrow leads to genuine repentance for sinning against the righteous God and there is a change of heart, we change our mind and God changes our hearts and regenerates us from the inside out. God is deadly serious about sin, when we genuinely repent we hate sin just as God hates it, and we turn away from it.
"But God commended His love toward us, in that while we were yet sinners Christ died for us." Romans 5:8 BELIEVE IN YOUR HEART THAT JESUS CHRIST DIED FOR YOUR SINS, WAS BURIED, AND THAT GOD RAISED JESUS FROM THE DEAD. This is trusting with all of your heart that Jesus Christ is who he said he was. He saves us from sin and hell and brings us into a relationship with him. We become God's children. We are saved from hell, eternal death.
"For whosoever shall call on the name of the Lord shall be saved." Romans 10:13 CALL UPON THE NAME OF THE LORD. Every single person who ever lived since Adam will bend their knee and confess with their mouth that Jesus Christ is Lord, the Lord of Lords and the King of Kings.
Read the Bible, Walk with the Lord and give your life to Him!

author: @jaclynfoster4511
text:
This is a musical masterpiece. I am new to Postie's music because...well my own ignorance. I judged. I judged him by his appearance and wow, what a mistake. I myself have been judged by my appearance for my whole life post puberty. It is hurtful, damaging, ignorant, and it's unacceptable. I want to apologize for doing the same thing to Post Malone that was done to me causing irreparable damage to my self esteem and the way I have valued myself since I was 11 years old. I'm 42 now and people still judge and label me  based on my appearance. I will never let myself do that to another human being ever again. 
This man is a genius. A true musician. A gentleman. A beautiful human being. A legend. Go Postie go!!

author: @sniffcats
text: This album very very recently was with me through one of the hardest times of my life that I’m still trying to heal from. The month of August was so brutal. And I was listening to this album every single day on repeat through it. I think I have to say… this might be one of my favorite albums of all time and it hurts so much that I can’t listen to it right now because of the pain associated. I hope as I heal it will become less painful for me to listen to this album considering I love it so much and it means so much to me. Music is insanely powerful and it’s a gift to be able to connect with people so deeply the way Post does 💗

author: @GregsWineStories
text: Post has had an album for each important time of my life, and especially the last three albums. In 2019, he released Hollywood Bleeding in early September when I was leaving France and my dad while not knowing I would stay 3 years not seeing him (I live in China, and Covid would stop all possibility of travel only a few months later). Post released Twelve Carat Toothache last year just when my dad was diagnosed with Pancreatic Cancer and Austin came out less than a month after my dad passed away. I don't believe in any sign or anything, but all of this gave Postie's songs a very deep meaning in my heart.
